### Create a menu (happy path).
### Requires a Bearer token from Authentication/Register.http or Authentication/Login.http
### and a {{hostId}} from Hosts/CreateHost.http (the calling user must own the host —
### resource auth via IAuthorizeResource<Host> per Cookbook Recipe 7).

@token = yourtoken
@hostId = 019E955C-89A3-7F92-A289-35F8823BC135

POST {{host}}/hosts/{{hostId}}/menus/create?api-version=2022-10-01
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Muffins R Us",
    "description": "Menu for Muffins R Us",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Muffins",
            "description": "The Muffins section",
            "items": [
                { "name": "Blueberry", "description": "A Blueberry Muffin" },
                { "name": "Chocolate", "description": "A Chocolate Muffin" },
                { "name": "Lemon",     "description": "A Lemon Muffin" }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Not Muffins",
            "description": "Anything that is not a muffin",
            "items": [
                { "name": "Cookie",  "description": "Probably oatmeal raisin or something" },
                { "name": "Cupcake", "description": "Its trying to be a muffin, but its not fooling anyone" }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

### Expected response shape:
### HTTP/1.1 201 Created
### Location: /hosts/{hostId}/menus/{menuId}
### Content-Type: application/json
### {
###   "id":             "019e955c-8a14-7b4c-8b40-f82ffb3b05f1",
###   "name":           "Muffins R Us",
###   "description":    "Menu for Muffins R Us",
###   "averageRating":  null,
###   "sections":       [ { "id":"...", "name":"Muffins", "description":"...", "items":[ ... ] }, ... ],
###   "hostId":         "019e955c-89a3-7f92-a289-35f8823bc135",
###   "dinnerIds":      [],
###   "menuReviewIds":  []
### }
###
### Capture the response `id` into `@menuId = ...` in Menus/GetMenu.http, UpdateMenu.http,
### and ListMenus.http for subsequent reads/updates.
###
### Failure modes:
###   - Invalid nested section / item (empty name or description) -> 422 with per-field
###     violations (see CreateMenu-InvalidNested.http).
###   - Caller does not own the route host -> 403 with code "menus.owner".
